The **Universal Gizmo** is a transform widget designed for moving, rotating, and scaling Actors when working in VR mode. 

![](universalgizmo.png)(w:400)

The elements of the Universal Gizmo are colored Red, Green, and Blue representing the X, Y, and Z axes, respectively.

| Action | Manipulator | Usage |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Translate** | ![](universalgizmo_move.png)(w:192) | Aim the controller at one of the translation manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to move the selected Actor(s) along the axis. |
| **Translate Plane** | ![](universalgizmo_moveplane.png)(w:192) | Aim the controller at one of the translation plane manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to move the selected Actor(s) along the plane (in 2 axes). |
| **Rotate** | ![](universalgizmo_rotate.png)(w:192) | Aim the controller at one of the rotation manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to rotate the selected Actor(s) around the axis. |
| **Scale** | ![](universalgizmo_scale.png)(w:192) | Aim the controller at one of the scale manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to scale the selected Actor(s) along the Y-axis. |
| **Uniform Scale** | ![](universalgizmo_uniformscale.png)(w:192) | Aim the controller at one of the stretch manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to scale the selected Actor(s) along all axes uniformly. |
| **Stretch** | ![](universalgizmo_stretch.png)(w:192) | Aim the controller at one of the stretch manipulators and squeeze the **Trigger** halfway to grab it. Move the controller to scale the selected Actor(s) non-uniformly along all axes while remaining anchored to the opposite corner. |
